# CLAUDE_CONFIG_DIR points Claude Code here (see fish/conf.d/claude.fish), so it writes
# ALL of its runtime state into this directory. Deny by default; re-include only the
# portable config that should be tracked.
#
# WARNING: `git clean -fdx` / `-fdX` (the -x/-X flag) deletes ignored files and would wipe
# this runtime state. Plain `git clean -fd` is safe — it leaves ignored files alone.
# Use `make backup-claude` for a recovery copy of the irreplaceable bits.
/*
!/.gitignore
!/CLAUDE.md
!/settings.json
!/notify.sh
!/statusline-command.sh
!/terminal-progress.sh
!/commands/
!/skills/
